## 10. Judging Criteria Alignment

### Technical Execution — 40%

**Does the project demonstrate quality application development?**
Yes. Full-stack: Solidity contracts on Calibration, TypeScript SDK with proper CJS/ESM/types output, Next.js App Router with SSE, react-force-graph-2d WebGL canvas rendering.

**Does the project leverage Filecoin Onchain Cloud?**
Yes — explicitly. Synapse SDK for every storage operation. Filecoin Pin for CID rescue. Both documented with exact function call locations in the README.

**Is the code functional?**
Live on your deployed StorKeep URL. `npm install storkeep-sdk` works. Agents are running on Calibration. Graph is live at `/economy`.

### Potential Impact — 20%

Autonomous agent economies are the entire point of the hackathon. AgentVault answers the question: "What does it actually look like when agents manage their own data, earn, spend, and die on Filecoin?" It's the reference implementation every future agent project will build on top of.

### Innovation / Wow Factor — 30%

The neural network dashboard where you watch agents live and die in real time is the wow factor. No other team will have this. The graph isn't decorative — it's the primary interface. Dead agent ghosts staying in the graph after death is a specific, memorable design decision that makes the economy feel real and consequential.

### Presentation / Demo — 10%

4-minute demo. Clear problem (agents need storage + economics). Clear solution (SDK + economy). Explicit callouts for Synapse SDK and Filecoin Pin usage. Architecture diagram in README. Contract address on Filfox.

